<item>
            <title>[DERBY-6411] Minimal select privilege should be checked in subqueries</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-6411</link>
                <project id="10594" key="DERBY">Derby</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-4191&quot; title=&quot;Lack of SELECT privilege does not prevent SELECT COUNT(*)&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;DERBY-4191&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;DERBY-4191&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; added checks for minimal select privilege in cases where a SELECT query didn&apos;t access any actual column in the base table, such as SELECT COUNT&lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/star_yellow.gif&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt; FROM USER1.T and SELECT 1 FROM USER1.T. That privilege checking is only done for top-level SELECT statements. It should also be done for subqueries.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Examples of queries where Derby does not currently check for minimal select privileges on the accessed tables (performed as USER2, which has no privileges on any of USER1&apos;s tables):&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;SELECT * FROM (SELECT COUNT&lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/star_yellow.gif&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt; FROM USER1.T) S&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;SELECT 1 FROM USER1.T UNION SELECT 2 FROM USER1.T&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;INSERT INTO USER2.T SELECT 1 FROM USER1.T&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I believe that the above statements should have failed, but currently they succeed.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
